[Questname] Right on the mine
[NPC Name] Amidison Stronghand
[Checkup] 2014-01-01
[Authors] Dudu and Lele

[Need] [Item] 5, Iron Ores; [Item] 5, Clacker meats

[To] Amidison Stronghand

[NPC Internal] I see many Stonebreakers in Hydlaa, why are they so busy?
[NPC] Amidison: Stonebreakers are always busy.
[NPC Narrate] -Amidison stares at you with a faint smile.-
[NPC] Amidison: But, yes, lately I heard some rumors I'd like to check.
[NPC] Amidison: Do you want to help me?
[NPC Internal] Yes, why not, there could be something worth to learn.
[NPC Narrate] -Amidison hair waves in the air while she nods.-
[NPC] Amidison: Go to Hamel Warson, here in Hydlaa plaza.
[NPC] Amidison: Ask him if he has any jobs for you.
[NPC] Amidison: Do what he asks, and see if you can find anything.

[To] Hamel Warson

[NPC Internal] I'd like to work for you.
[NPC] Hamel: So you've been listening to gossip?
[NPC] Hamel: And you're assuming I'm searching for workers.
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel raises a hand to stop any answer.-
[NPC] Hamel: You want to be busy?
[NPC] Hamel: I have no problem with that.
[NPC] Hamel: I need provisions and minerals, you can get them for me.
[NPC Internal] Let's start with the mineral, how much and where can I find it?
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel nods.-
[NPC] Hamel: I need five units of Iron Ore.
[NPC] Hamel: You can buy it from any miner, here in Hydlaa.
[NPC] Hamel: Otherwise you should ask various merchants.
[NPC Internal] Which kind of provision, and how much?
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel nods and raises his thumb.-
[NPC] Hamel: Some food.
[NPC] Hamel: Ask Rolara Hammersong, I have a sort of arrangement with her.
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel raises his forefinger.-
[NPC] Hamel: And some beer.
[NPC] Hamel: For that ask Narwin Molstagh, alas it seems he doesn't like our arrangement anymore, maybe you'll need to be creative.
[NPC] Hamel: And…
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel looks into your eyes.-
[NPC] Hamel: Don't ask anyone else.
[NPC] Hamel: Only Rolara and Narwin.
[NPC] Hamel: Return when you've both beer and food provisions.

[To] Narwin Molstagh

[NPC Internal] I have the five units of Iron for you.
[NPC] Narwin: Oh, I'm so glad to see an honest Enkidukai.
[NPC Narrate] -Narwin picks a big sack from within a group of bags on the floor, he gives it to you.-
[NPC] Narwin: A honest payment for an awesome job well done.

[To] Rolara Hammersong

[NPC Internal] Hamel told me…
[NPC Narrate] -Rolara stops working and snorts.-
[NPC] Rolara: Hamel…
[NPC] Rolara: Hamel…
[NPC] Rolara: Hamel.
[NPC] Rolara: How am I supposed to work so fast?
[NPC] Rolara: I gave the last shipment to one of Hamel's delivery boys.
[NPC] Rolara: I finished the raw materials, and I am late for the other contracts.
[NPC Internal] There has to be something I can do for you.
[NPC Narrate] -Rolara bits her lips, looking at you.-
[NPC] Rolara: Yes.
[NPC] Rolara: Sure.
[NPC] Rolara: Let's try your way, go and find me five pieces of Clacker meat.
[NPC] Rolara: I will prepare them for you.
[NPC] Rolara: They will make nice provisions.
[NPC Internal] Here is the Clacker meat you asked for.
[NPC] Rolara: I don't like to work for Hamel.
[NPC Narrate] -Rolara washes her hands in a bowl, then she takes the meat from you. She starts cutting and slicing it.-
[NPC] Rolara: I'm doing it only because it seems the only thing to do to support us.
[NPC] Rolara: No.
[NPC] Rolara: Don't ask.
[NPC] Rolara: Time is running.
[NPC Narrate] -Rolara finishes packing the meat and hands you the provisions.-
[NPC] Rolara: Here you go.

[To] Narwin Molstagh

[NPC Internal] Hamel sent me for the beer.
[NPC] Narwin: I was expecting someone like you.
[NPC Narrate] -Narwin sits on a little barrel.-
[NPC] Narwin: But I will repeat what I told the last one.
[NPC] Narwin: I quit.
[NPC] Narwin: I don't work for Hamel anymore.
[NPC Internal] May I ask why you want to quit?
[NPC] Narwin: Why?
[NPC] Narwin: Why are you asking me?
[NPC Narrate] -Narwin raises a fist, his face twisted in rage.-
[NPC] Narwin: Even though I don't mind how bad things are, there are some things we should never do.
[NPC] Narwin: And if he dares to ask Nal…
[NPC Narrate] -Narwin snorts and grins.-
[NPC] Narwin: No.
[NPC] Narwin: I will only quit, I will not betray anyone.
[NPC] Narwin: This is none of your business.
[NPC] Narwin: Leave me.

[Info] Talking to Hamel is optional at this point

[To] Hamel Warson

[NPC Narrate] Narwin refused to help, may I know why?
[NPC] Hamel Warson drums his fingers on his beard.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: Narwin thinks a warrior should only drink beer, not create it.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: Silly, isn't it?
[NPC] Hamel Warson opens his arms, surrendering.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: If you can't get him to work, never mind.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: I will find someone else to persuade him.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: Maybe someone prettier.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: Just let me know if you think you can't handle this.
[NPC Narrate] Why do you need this material?
[NPC] Hamel Warson: I can answer: none of your business.
[NPC] Hamel Warson sighs.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: But people like you usually imagine nasty plots and things like this.
[NPC] Hamel Warson shakes his head.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: Hydlaa is full of people who want a job.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: I'm simply using this workforce to expand my business.
[NPC Narrate] Let's start with the mineral, how much and where can I find it?
[NPC] Hamel Warson nods.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: I need five units of Iron Ore.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: You can buy it from any miner, here in Hydlaa.
[NPC] Hamel Warson: Otherwise you should ask various merchants.

[To] Nalri Grimtorr

[NPC Internal] I need to persuade Narwin to give me some beer for Hamel, can you help me?
[NPC] Nalri: So Narwin is still making trouble.
[NPC Narrate] -Nalri puts her hand on her hip.-
[NPC] Nalri: I will solve this.
[NPC] Nalri: Tell him I don't want to quarrel again.
[NPC] Nalri: He will do his work.
[NPC] Nalri: As always.

[To] Narwin Molstagh

[NPC Internal] Nalri told me that you must do your job.
[NPC] Narwin: Again.
[NPC] Narwin: Nalri!
[NPC Narrate] -Narwin sighs sadly.-
[NPC] Narwin: I hate this attitude.
[NPC] Narwin: Do you know why…
[NPC Narrate] -Narwin stops talking and looks down.-
[NPC] Narwin: Sorry, I can't break my word.
[NPC] Narwin: But I want to let you know that I'm doing this only because otherwise Hamel will use Nalri in his schemes.
[NPC] Narwin: People like Cilay Mecur would never accept behavior like this.
[NPC Narrate] -Narwin grinds his teeth.-
[NPC] Narwin: If Hamel asks you to go to Gugrontid don't follow his orders.
[NPC] Narwin: Go there and talk with Gardr Keck instead.
[NPC] Narwin: You will understand.
[NPC Narrate] -Narwin stands up and gives you the barrel, his demeanor changing to a smirk.-
[NPC] Narwin: Here, take this barrel.
[NPC] Narwin: I call it…
[NPC Narrate] -He moves his hand through the air mimicing a marquee.-
[NPC] Narwin: Narwing Beer.
[NPC] Narwin: Catchy, don't 'cha think?
[NPC Internal] Who is Cilay Mecur?
[NPC] Narwin: One who would never accept…
[NPC Narrate] -Narwin chest enlarges while he inhales. Then he takes a long sigh.-
[NPC] Narwin: A Keeper of the Hammer.
[NPC] Narwin: I haven't seen him in a long time.

[To] Hamel Warson

[NPC Internal] The beer and the provisions you asked.
[NPC] Hamel: That's very, very, nice of you.
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel nods, licking his lips.-
[NPC] Hamel: Please accept this as a reward for your job.
[NPC Internal] Do you need anything else?
[NPC] Hamel: Uhm.
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel stares at you, his pupils growing wide.-
[NPC] Hamel: I think that I can use someone like you.
[NPC] Hamel: Honest and efficient.
[NPC] Hamel: But this last work needs also discretion.
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel raises a hand.-
[NPC] Hamel: And if you accept you can't quit anymore from the job, I need you to finish this.
[NPC] Hamel: Can you handle this?
