[NPC] Hamel: I need you to get something for me.
[NPC] Hamel: But if other people find out about this…
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel sighs and closes his eyes for a moment.-
[NPC] Hamel: Some people want to steal ancient artifacts.
[NPC] Hamel: Hammer artifacts.
[NPC] Hamel: I found them, but they are too spread in a large territory.
[NPC] Hamel: If anything slips your tongue my enemies will undestand everything.
[NPC] Hamel: They know you work for me, and if you start asking they will put the pieces together.
[NPC] Hamel: I can't risk that.
[NPC Internal] Very well, tell me what you need.
[NPC] Hamel: I will be brief.
[NPC Narrate] -Hamel licks his lips.-
[NPC] Hamel: Go to Gugrontid.
[NPC] Hamel: Find a Nolthrir named Lyrus Lospur.
[NPC] Hamel: She is expecting you.
[NPC] Hamel: Take the package and return it to me.
[NPC] Hamel: You can look in the package if you wish.

[To] Lyrus Lospur

[NPC Internal] Hamel sent me here.
[NPC] Lyrus: I was expecting you.
[NPC Narrate] -Lyrus takes out a list from her vest, checks it then looks at you. She takes a package from under a sheet.-
[NPC] Lyrus: This is for you.

